    <p>This is my first Raspberry Pi project. The goal of this project is to use Raspberry Pi to automate my home fish tank (72 gallon) operation. 
        As the first iteration of this  project, I had implemented 6 sensors, 1 water pump control based on pre-set schedule, and a water pump delay switch.
    </p>
    
    <img src="~/Client/otherSensorDesign.png" style="float:right;" />
    <p>
        The sensor electronic circuitry is very sensitive. If one PNP transistor can amplify  the signal 200 times, by chaining  the 2 transistors, we have 40,000 (200*200) signal
        amplification. It is so sensitive, it can even sense the hand touch the wire. Alternative design can be used if adjustment of sensitivity level is required. (see diagram on the right)
        
        The current sensor implementation is highly sensitive and not adjustable, therefore it has some noises in the log (by clicking any sensor in the home page).
        
    </p>
    
